<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:227px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Nichiren_statue_Japan.jpg" class="image" title="A statue of Nichiren outside Honnoji in the Teramachi District of Kyoto."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/1/1d/Nichiren_statue_Japan.jpg/225px-Nichiren_statue_Japan.jpg" width="225" height="300" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Nichiren_statue_Japan.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
A statue of Nichiren outside Honnoji in the Teramachi District of <a href="/wiki/Kyoto" title="Kyoto">Kyoto</a>.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><b>Nichiren</b> (<a href="/wiki/Japanese_language" title="Japanese language">Japanese</a>: <span lang="ja" xml:lang="ja">日蓮</span>) (<span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1222-02-16"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="02-16"><a href="/wiki/February_16" title="February 16">February 16</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1222" title="1222">1222</a></span> – <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1282-10-13"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="10-13"><a href="/wiki/October_13" title="October 13">October 13</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1282" title="1282">1282</a></span>) was a <a href="/wiki/Buddhism" title="Buddhism">Buddhist</a> monk who lived during the <a href="/wiki/Kamakura_period" title="Kamakura period">Kamakura period</a> (<a href="/wiki/1185" title="1185">1185</a>-<a href="/wiki/1333" title="1333">1333</a>) in <a href="/wiki/Japan" title="Japan">Japan</a>. Nichiren taught devotion to the <a href="/wiki/Lotus_Sutra" title="Lotus Sutra">Lotus Sutra</a>, <a href="/wiki/Nam_Myoho_Renge_Kyo" title="Nam Myoho Renge Kyo" class="mw-redirect">Nam-Myōhō-Renge-Kyō</a>, as the exclusive means to attain enlightenment and the chanting of "Nam Myo ho Renge Kyo" as the essential practice of the teaching. He is credited with founding what has come to be known as <a href="/wiki/Nichiren_Buddhism" title="Nichiren Buddhism">Nichiren Buddhism</a>, a major school of <a href="/wiki/Japanese_Buddhism" title="Japanese Buddhism" class="mw-redirect">Japanese Buddhism</a> encompassing numerous sects espousing diverse doctrines.</p>
